You Are Cherry Pie
You're the perfect combo of innocent and sexy.
At times, you seem a bit naive, simple, and innocent.
But at second glance, you are sensual, seductive, and even a little naughty.
You have people fooled - at least you'd like to think so.

Those who like you enjoy a contradiction.
Either that, or they can't really make up their minds about what they want.
And you can usually give people what they want... as long as you're in the mood.
You've been known to be quite tempestuous, and pleasing others is not high on your list of priorities.
What Kind of Pie Are You?
i still hate that 'sweet cherry pie' song tho.

dear brain,
                       as you are no doubt aware, we do not live in harrogate. we live in manchester. there are several very good reasons for this, the main one being that harrogate is BORING. i know it's so very beautiful and green and hilly and the air smells nice, and there are many shops that sell cute cheap random happy crap within walking distance of your house, but remember that the bars are all overpriced and trendy (which you can only take in small doses) and you have no friends here because they all had the good sense to piss off elsewhere too. i understand you never spend longer than 2 nites here and thus you forget all this, but stay any longer and you'll not only remember all too clearly, you'll also start to pine for the pretty boy that lives in our bed in manchester. of course, you'll be fed beef n roast potatoes, yorskhire pudding and gravy before we leave. and more tea. thank you for your co-operation.

P.S. notice the hayfever is twice as nasty here. my head and throat are fookin sore. the magic pills are back in manchester cos you let me forget to bring them didn't you? bah.

You Are Cookie Monster
Misunderstood as a primal monster, you're a true hedonist with a huge sweet tooth. You are usually feeling: Hungry. Cookies are preferred, but you'll eat anything if cookies aren't around. You are famous for: Your slightly crazy eyes and usual way of speaking How you life your life: In the moment. "Me want COOKIE!"
The Sesame Street Personality Quiz

Your Result: Science/Math Nerd

underwear, 1 pair jeans, 1 vest top, 1 big thick Sorrowkiller tshirt, 1 pair knee socks, 1 pair thick bedsocks, 1 big thick dressing gown with hood up, 1 pair fingerless gloves, 1 duvet and 1 hot water bottle. the heating went out again :(

i don't normally like the one-sleeved look, but this dress ---> http://www.moonmaiden-gothic-clothing.co.uk/moonmaiden-index/gowns/mmg46/mmg46.htm is gorgeous. and i didn't think i liked velvet, but i keep being proved wrong.

that is all.

i'm wearing 3 (i repeat: three) pairs of socks and my feet are still fookin freezing

i noticed a while ago that i'd never seen a tesco in harrogate. today the other magic glowy picture box in my lounge (ie the tv) confirmed it: harrogate is one of only 4 postcodes in the uk without a tesco- the other 3 being orkney, the shetlands, the outer hebrides. i don't know why that makes me feel all warm inside, but it does.

last nite was so much fun =) and now i have cake!
the plan for tonite seems to be Grand Central around 9-9:30ish, then rock world later

well, i made it through another new year without killing anyone(though i had to fight to surpress the urges), and i didn't even cheat by spending it asleep. i went out in reality. and survived. i still hate new year. i stayed up all nite playing board games (i blame slev), got to bed around half 12 yesterday afternoon and slept for 21 hours- a new record for me. though i did have a 3 hour break for breakfast at 1am, but only cos i hadn't had anything resembling a meal for 24 hours before that. sleeping pattern needs fixing. i still blame slev. i bought new pyjamas, they're pink. they feel wrong but they were the least ugly ones in la senza (it had to be la senza cos i had gift vouchers). the old pyjamas are at least 3 years old and have recently developed a giant hole in the backside. they served me well :( well i'm boring myself so i'm gonna go sleep. i shouldn't be tired but i am

whilst looking through past entries to see whether i'd already used the song line "the way we were is the way i wanna be" as a subject line (i had. damn) i noticed that all my posts over the last year fit on the first page of my journal. which means i really should talk crap on here more often. so... yeah... reality. not as sucky as it could be considering i'm unemployed again, as i haven't run out of money yet. last nite i went to see levellers (fookin brilliant) and last week i went to see tool (even better, amazing, wow etc...) and had really good nites out after both. going to see iron maiden soon, can't remember what possessed me to think it was a good idea at the time but i have a feeling it was blond. apart from that all i've really been doing is sleeping- 12 hours a nite can't be healthy can it? but i can't help it. must be something wrong with me. speaking of which, head hurts and bed is luring me. so more tea then sleep. mmm.
if there's anything that can't be fixed (or at least eased) by a cup of tea then i don't want to know about it

given that i always hear guys complaining that "women say they want nice guys but they really want bastards", i thought i should public express my opinion on the subject: there is no such thing as nice guys*. they're just idiots who are better at hiding their bastardness for longer. say at least a few months. at least with bastards you know what to expect rather than being tricked into trusing someone. then it hurts more when they fuck you over.

*with the exception, of course, of slev and his infinite superhuman patience and general all-round lovely fluffyness. and slight bastardness, but in the good way**

**apologies if i made anyone puke

and dan, if you still exist on lj, happy birfday x

i have 2 choices: jobhunt or curl up in bed n sleep.

jobhunting will be so much less of a chore when i don't have to be up at 5am for work.

i watched the omen on saturday nite and now every morning when i walk past the creepy unlit church in the dark i have to check there isn't a long spike on the top that's gonna impale me. nothing i can do about the potential men with knives in the trees/ zombies in the graveyard tho. lack of sleep makes me paranoid, especially at 6am.

i shut up now.

i haven't laid eyes on a tesco since saturday

so harrgoate does have its plus points

the tea tastes better with yorkshire water too
i found online puerto rico! it's not like i wanted to sleep anyway...

booyeah 9 day weekend. i love paid holiday =D

in other news, i need to kill off some brain cells (ie the stupid ones, they're taking over). time to start drinkin again

today my snot is blue. and my fingers are too. i wanted to be a smurf but... [insert line ending with something that rhymes with blue. my poetry skills are lacking]

in other news, my mum got rid of the cool purple carpet in my room- it was older than me and had a melted wax scorch mark- and replaced it with laminate flooring. wrong.

my face has become one giant snot party this week. at least it's friday (in my head at least, they made me work today so my brain got all confused by the being up and dressed and out before noon. so very wrong.) oh well, yay week off begins now. and given that it's friday nite, my rightful place is in bed with tea. oh yeah, i'm so hardcore...

1. i love that hippy smell that comes with buying clothes from hobgoblin. i wanted to be glowy.

2. stationery shops own me.

3. my mum broke the toilet. she fell off it. we now have no cold water cos she had to turn it off to stop  the bathroom flooding. i'm leaving before the kettle runs out of water (ie tomorrow afternoon)

today i walked in on slev wearing a bright green vest. i was so terrified i ran away and am now hiding out in harrogate, in the hopes that when i dare go back he'll be back to his all-black self.

since i'm here i've dragged out my old guitar. i need it for a perplexcity card. i'm trying to learn to read guitar tab, seems simple enough.

i'm tired and hungry

proof i lost my mind, part 13309. or something. i lost count years ago.

i'm gonna see iron maiden in december. again. of my own free will (tho i suspect someone's influence at work here). and i'm even paying for my own ticket. i should bring toast. at least it's in manchester this time.

slev, you owe me for your ticket. which i'm more than happy to accept in the form of something black and shiny <----*unsubtle hint here, look!* =D

i should go to work now. meh.

this week i learned that dropping my phone in a puddle is not the way to make it behave. i've bounced it off the floor many times over the years and it's survived, this time it tried make a break for freedom. and was thwarted. it should consider its delicate self lucky i got to it before the bus wheels did. so i may or may not have to buy (as in, pay actual money for!) another phone/clock/personal brain organiser, but i'd rather this one didn't die. at first i thought it had gone, but after it dried out it worked fine. today it's been mostly functional, apart from the screen freezing and total battery death. i never let my battery die, it isn't a good sign.

not much else has been happening. i think i should stay away from the solventy things at work, i hallucinate too much these days. slightly worrying. oh, and i went to see coheed and cambria last month and never got round to posting about it afterwards. all i'm saying now is "so gooooood"

what's that you say? sleep? ok, why not. hope everybody's shinypeachy happychildren x

present haul so far: one from the most lovelyest of husbandness (metallica dvd, yay), one from his parents (a supercute bear and an ice cream sundae kit) and one from my mammy (beautiful shiny watch). and money from the pappy. i luff presents =D

*must go to work. must not spend all day in my pyjamas playing games*
the upside of having to get up at 4:30am last week is that i get lie ins this week

there needs to be a way of drinkin tea and eating cookies while still keeping arms wrapped in the duvet and head on the pillow. i had to sit up =( ah well, it's still all peachy goodness. i love sleep

i am soon-to-be no longer unemployed slacker dole scum. i'm back to being the regular kind of skank kitten scum =D
do i sleep, or do i drink tea? i've been up since 6am, and didn't get to sleep till around 3 last nite. i'm going with teadrinkin. don't have to be up till 10 tomorrow. mmm lie ins

i'm sick enough to get the nice insanity brain mushyness i enjoy so much and can justify spending 12 hours a day sleeping (and still need to nap in the afternoon) but i'm not so sick i can't do anything. perfect. and when the brain stops aching i can buy cough syrup. for now i have hot lemonade. ahh the fun side of a sore throat

slev has no idea who david beckham is. normally this would be reason enough to disown a boy. though with this one, the ability to live in his own little world and totally ignore reality is one of the reasons i love him. still, this is going a little too far. he must be destroyed. uh, i mean educated. yes, educated... mwahahaha...
i'm an angel. see the proof =D
ahh sitting wrapped in a duvet listening to metallica with tea n cookies. and within falling distance of the bed. its how antisocial friday nites should be.

just proving i still exist. though i still have no life to write about. so i decided i should become a cult leader, as i'm amassing more loyal minions than i know what to do with. anyone wanna join? mullets may be involved. you know you want to. my horoscope today warned me about the "chicken of doom". made me think of jules oh, and for those that didn't get the memo, the husband has been relegated to the role of boyfriend. sucks to be him. i like this =D

http://www.hottopic.com/store/product.asp?LS=0&ITEM=270910 all i can say is "ooh, baby..."

there was a pretty green moth in my bathroom earlier this week. i called it wormy. then it died. poor wormy :(

damn i'm tired. and i need to shower. and sleep. and wake up in a big pile of money. and sleep. oh yeah.
